<episodedetails><title>Attazione D’Amore</title><plot>In The four parts of this film, renowned conductor Riccardo Chaily and Mahler’s internationally acclaimed biographer Henry-Louis de la Grange analyse the four movements of this masterful musical piece. Reaching into the heart of Mahler’s music, the film marks Riccardo Chailly’s celebration of his departure from Amsterdam’s Royal Concertgebouw Orchestra in June 2004, after sixteen years of close collaboration.</plot></episodedetails>